# Insta AutoDM — Locked Project

Monorepo at `C:\Users\brije\Desktop\insta dm`. MVP SaaS: auto-send Instagram DMs on keyword comments.

## Stack

- Frontend: Next.js 15, TypeScript, Tailwind (`frontend/`)
- Backend: Express 5, Prisma, PostgreSQL (`backend/`)
- Local dev uses **portable Node + portable PostgreSQL** (no Docker/admin on this machine)

## Start / restart

```powershell
# Full stack
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File ".\scripts\dev.ps1"

# Fix blank/500 login page (corrupted .next or hung port 3000)
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File ".\scripts\restart-frontend.ps1"
```

Node PATH prefix: `$env:LOCALAPPDATA\node-portable\node-v22.16.0-win-x64`

## URLs & demo login

- Frontend: http://localhost:3000
- Login: http://localhost:3000/login
- Backend: http://localhost:4000
- Demo: `demo@instaautodm.com` / `demo1234` (one-click button on login page)

## Architecture notes

- Dashboard metrics use mock data in `frontend/src/lib/demo-data.ts` (presentation only)
- Keyword rules CRUD hits real backend API
- CORS allows both `localhost:3000` and `127.0.0.1:3000`
- Do not change backend unless explicitly requested

## Common failures

| Symptom | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Login page 500 / timeout | `restart-frontend.ps1` |
| "Failed to fetch" on login | Backend down or CORS origin mismatch |
| Edit/delete rules silent fail | Backend down; check http://localhost:4000/health |

